Pre-Game Insights: Zambia are chasing their first win in the tournament since their improbable triumph in 2012
Morocco are targeting their second AFCON title in history
Others: Zambia have only beaten Morocco once in six meetings, losing three times and drawing twice
Morocco have not been slouches defensively, conceding just two shots on target from the 12 they have faced
Zambia will be without Rodrick Kabwe, who will serve a one-match suspension for his dismissal against Tanzania
Sofiane Boufal for Abde Ezzalzouli was the only change made by Regragui from Morocco's opener
